title: For Sale/Trade:  Converted Saiga .308
location: Union Mills, Charlotte, Asheville, Asheville, North Carolina
postcontent:
I bought this rifle as a project. I picked it up used at a gun show. Now I need to sell it for car parts money, picked up a new beater and it needs some work. It does show some wear here and there and has a few scratches, especially on the handguard from the sling swivel. Not sure on the round count, but the rifling looks very good. The rifle is completely functional except for the safety. It needs to either have a selector from a standard AK or have the current selector built back up. The selector swap is very simple and a selector can be picked up for $20 shipped from apex gun parts. If you can take down an ak to clean the barrel, you can change the selector out. 

The parts used in the conversion are a Dinzag Arms trigger guard, Hogue grip, tapco G2 trigger group modified with spacer to fit the Saiga .308, and an ATI butt stock. I retained the factory bolt hold open. If you don't like the buttstock, I have a standard Tapco adjustable I can toss on there. The butt stock's cheekrest pad/sticker has a scratch on it and is less than $10 to replace.  Here's a link to one.
http://www.opticsplanet.com/advanced-technologies-soft-touch-cheekrest-pad-for-shotforce-cheekrest.html


It comes with the 10 round magazine that is pictured.

Asking $850 OBO

Only trade interest would be a Ruger LC9, Diamondback DB9, or a SCCY plus cash. I'll listen to other offers.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Mech Tech .357 Sig Glock Carbine Upper
postcontent:
Mech Tech .357 Sig Glock Carbine Upper.
If you have a full size Glock in .40 S&W or .357 SIG, this is the upper you’ve been looking for!

In case you did not know, the .40 S&W and the .357 Sig use the same case.  The same round will fit & function in either magazine.  By changing out the barrel to the appropriate caliber your full size Glock can fire either caliber!

This ad is for a Mech Tech carbine upper in .357 Sig.  Shoots .357 Sig only!  Turn your full size Glock in .40 S&W or .357 Sig into a .357 Sig Carbine!  The upper comes as shown with BSA Red Dot site and CAA vertical fore-grip.
Clean and reliable blow back operation and a real blast to shoot. This is one of the rare adjustable /collapsible stock versions.  This is a legal rifle configuration for the Glock lower because you’re putting on a stock AND a 16 inch barrel all in one. Just putting a stock on a pistol is a big no-no. When assembled (real easy, anybody can do it) the manufacturer claims a 40% increase in muzzle velocity.  Simply remove your full size Glock upper, add the extended feed ramp (which just drops in & I’m including 2 of them) to the lower and then slide & lock the carbine upper onto the lower rails as you would during normal assembly.  Disassembly is the same as removing the normal Glock upper. NO special tools needed.
I’m also including two 30 round mags (not shown in photos) that will also take .357 or .40 S&W as noted above.
$450.00
Thanks for looking.

The sharp rise in recent home invasions in Eastern North Carolina has earned the attention of residents. Here’s your chance to learn both how to prevent becoming the victim of a violent crime and what to do if you’re forced to react to a home invasion.

Like a fire in the home, nobody every thinks it will happen to them. Yet almost every home has fire extinguishers and smoke detectors. The time to learn what you should do is before something happens.

You will also learn strategies for responding to life-threatening encounters; how to detect criminal schemes and those with nefarious intentions, what you can do to prevent having to use deadly force, and finally, what you must know should you be forced to use it.
